![ProCogGraph Logo](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/bashton-lab/ProCogGraph/main/images/PROCOGGRAPH%20full%20logo%20v1.png)
Welcome to ProCogGraph! ProCogGraph is a graph-based cognate ligand-domain interaction database for exploring and mining domain-cognate ligand interactions.  
&nbsp;  
To get started, navigate to the search page and search for a PDB ID, domain, EC ID, or ligand. For more information on the methods employed by ProCogGraph, check out the [ProCogGraph repo](https://github.com/bashton-lab/ProCogGraph)  
&nbsp;  
Note: depending on screen resolution/DPI, the dashboard view can be either very small or very large and cluttered. CTRL/cmd +/- followed by a page refresh can be used to scale the dashboard appropriately for your monitor.

*Global Parameters:* Set the minimum similarity threshold for cognate ligands, select the domain database to use, and how to filter cognate ligands (Best = only cognate ligands with highest score, Any = all cognate ligands above the defined threshold, All: All bound entities are shown regardless of whether they have a cognate ligand match)  
&nbsp;  
*PDB Search:* Search for a structure by PDB ID. Results are displayed in the adjacent table. Click on a structure to be taken to the PDB search page with results for the structure.  
&nbsp;  
*EC ID Search* Search for an enzyme by EC ID, and view results including structures and cognate ligands.  
&nbsp;  
*Domain Search*  Search for a domain by Domain Accession - the grouping for a domain database (CATH, Gene3D = Homol. Superfam., Pfam = Family, SCOP/SUPERFAMILY/SCOP2-SF/SCOP2-FA = Superfamily)  
&nbsp;  
*Ligand Search* Search for a cognate ligand or bound entity by name or database cross-reference (free text field)

The domain summaries listed here provide information for **`$neodash_domain_desc`** ($neodash_domain_superfamily_id) at $neodash_parity_score_cutoff PARITY score cutoff.  
